South Africa  beat  New Zealand  1-0
in their best-of-three Test cricket series after the home team
avoided defeat in the final match in Wellington.  Morne Morkel took all six wickets as New Zealand reached
200-6 on day five at the Basin Reserve to secure the draw after
slumping to 83-5. Kane Williamson scored 102 not out to thwart
the touring teamâ€™s victory push.  AB de Villiers earlier struck 68 off 49 balls to lift South
Africa, which resumed at 75-0, to 189-3 in its second innings
before captain Graeme Smith declared to set up the victory
chance with his team 388 runs ahead.  The first Test in Dunedin was also drawn, while South
Africa won the second match at Hamilton by nine wickets.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
